## Lewis & Short data (Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0)

The Lewis & Short lexicon data (`data/lewis_short/`) and databases derived
from it are licensed under:

**Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International**
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

Per the Perseus availability statement, whenever you use the document you must
credit Perseus as follows:

> Text provided under a CC BY-SA license by Perseus Digital Library,
> http://www.perseus.tufts.edu, with funding from The National Endowment
> for the Humanities. Data accessed from https://github.com/PerseusDL/lexica/.

You must leave that availability statement intact, and offer Perseus any
modifications you make.

The morphology data (`data/analyses/`, derived from the Perseus/Morpheus
analyzer as packaged by Diogenes) is likewise Perseus-derived CC BY-SA
material.

---

## Ramshorn synonyms data (public domain)

Ramshorn, *Dictionary of Latin Synonymes*, translated by Francis Lieber
(Boston, 1841), is in the public domain. The OCR text was obtained from the
Internet Archive:
https://archive.org/details/ramshorn-lewis-dictionary-of-latin-synonymes-1841

---

## Spinelli–Fenzi near-synonyms data (CC BY)

Tommaso Spinelli & Giacomo Fenzi, *The First Online Dictionary of Latin
Near-Synonyms* (University of St Andrews, 2019), is licensed under
**Creative Commons Attribution** (CC BY).
Dataset: https://doi.org/10.17630/3cf644e6-86b8-44d0-a50a-b33c7ca86072
Source: https://github.com/tommasospinelli/Online-Dictionary-of-Latin-Near-Synonyms
The dataset is included in this repository at
`data/spinelli/latin_near_synonyms.json`.

---

## Allen & Greenough grammar data (Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0)

*Allen and Greenough's New Latin Grammar for Schools and Colleges* (ed.
Greenough, Kittredge, Howard, D'Ooge; Ginn & Company, 1903) is used here in
its original Perseus Digital Library TEI-XML digitization (not the later
Dickinson College Commentaries / Alpheios revision, which is CC BY-NC-SA and
therefore not redistributable in a commercial-compatible bundle like this
one). This Perseus edition is covered by the same CC BY-SA 4.0 terms and
Perseus attribution requirement as the Lewis & Short data above:
https://github.com/PerseusDL/canonical-pdlrefwk

---

## Summary

When distributing this dictionary:
1. Include/reference these licenses
2. Keep the Perseus attribution intact
3. Any derivative works using the Lewis & Short data must also be CC BY-SA 4.0
